# Observability And Security

- Generate a request ID for each request.
- Use structured `tracing` logs with fields rather than string-only logs.
- Redact prompt content by default.
- Never log API keys or Authorization headers.
- Never commit `.env` files.
- Track latency, success/failure, selected provider, fallback attempts, estimated tokens, and estimated cost.
- Keep in-memory metrics simple for the MVP.
- Use fixed-size buffers if storing recent request details in memory.
- Make full prompt logging an explicit local-development-only option.
- Prefer safe defaults in configuration.
- Metrics should eventually include totals, error rate, average and p95 latency, provider counts, token estimates, and cost estimates.
